-- Brazilian Stock Movers: Brookfield, Fibria Celulose and JBS
-- B y   D e n y s e   G o d o y
-- 2012-05-14T21:24:22Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-05-14/brazilian-stock-movers-brookfield-fibria-celulose-and-jbs.html
The following companies had  unusual 
price changes in  Sao Paulo  trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses, and prices are as of the close in Sao Paulo.
Preferred shares are usually the most-traded class of stock.  The  Bovespa (IBOV)  Index dropped 3.2 percent to 57,539.61.  Brookfield Incorporacoes SA (BISA3)  (BISA3 BS) lost 15 percent to
4.18 reais, the lowest since July 2009.  Brazil ’s fourth-largest
homebuilder by revenue reported that first-quarter profit
declined 94 percent to 4 million reais ($2.01 million) on higher
building costs and contract cancellations.  Fibria Celulose SA (FIBR3)  (FIBR3 BS) fell 1.9 percent to 14.17
reais. The world’s largest pulp declined to its lowest closing
price this year after reporting a net loss of 11 million reais
in the first quarter as prices for the paper-making material
declined.  JBS SA (JBSS3)  (JBSS3 BS) dropped 1.9 percent to 7.12 reais. Itau
BBA SA began coverage of the meatpacker, rating the stock
outperform, the equivalent of a buy. Poultry operations in the
U.S. and beef operations in Brazil are expected to be strong,
analyst Alexandre Ruiz Miguel wrote in a report to clients.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Denyse Godoy in Sao Paulo at 
